Package: pid.pos
Type: Package
Title: PID detection via NLP
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Robert", "Cook", email="rzc1@staff.staffs.ac.uk", 
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: The package maintainer <yourself@somewhere.net>
Description: A package for the detection and contextualization of personally 
    identifiable data (PID) in free text via natural language processing (NLP).  
    This package is a wraper to the 'english-ewt-2.5' UDPipe model intended to 
    extract 'proper nouns' and provide a report of their usage/ context in a 
    set of free text documents.  The main point of entry to the package is via 
    the `proper_noun_report` function (see `Troubleshooting` vignette for 
    possible issues with the automated downloading of the pretrained UDPipe 
    model).
